In the design of [[radio]] broadcast systems, especially [[television]] systems, the desired-to-undesired channel ratio ('''D/U ratio''') is a measure of the strength of the broadcast signal for a particular channel compared with the strength of undesired [[broadcast signal]]s in the same channel (e.g. from other nearby transmitting stations).

