In [[argumentation theory]], a '''term''' is that part of a statement in an argument which refers to a specific thing. Usually, but not always expressed as a [[noun]], one of the requirements to informally prove a conclusion with a [[deductive argument]] is for all its terms to be used [[unambiguous]]ly. The ambiguous use of a term in a deductive argument may be an instance of the [[fallacy of four terms]].

